# Fallback: hook-on Go client (AES-256-GCM plugin loaded)
# vs stock Go host (upstream SDK, no hook API)
# The stock host has no cipher-preferences header. The reference
# plugin only supports AES-256-GCM and rejects empty peer prefs
# (no ChaCha20 fallback). Both sides reject. A production plugin
# that supports both ciphers would fall back to ChaCha20 here.
CLIENT_VARIANT=hook-go
HOST_VARIANT=stock-go
CLIENT_PREFS=2
HOST_PREFS=
EXPECTED_OUTCOME=REJECT
